## Stochastic Trace Formula on Negatively Curved Manifolds

```math
\begin{aligned}
Z_{\Delta/2}(t) &= \mu(\Omega_t) = \int_M k_t((x,y),(x,y))\sqrt{g}dxdy + \sum_{\set{\text{closed geodesics }\gamma}} \mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) \\

\mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) &= \frac{e^{-\ell(\gamma)^2/2t}}{\sqrt{2\pi t}} \mu(e^{-\ell(\gamma)x(t)}\Omega_t^0[\gamma])\space\text{ by Girsanov}\\
\\
\small{\text{so the Radon-Nicodym Derivative along  }\gamma(t)\text{ is}}\\
\\
\frac{d\mu(e^{-\ell(\gamma)x(t)}
 \Omega^0_t[\gamma])}{\sqrt{g}dxdy}\vert_{\gamma(t)} &= \frac{1}{\sqrt{\det(I-P_\gamma)}}(1 + \frac{tK(\gamma(t))}{6}+O(t^2)) \space\text{by McKean and Singer}\\

\implies\\

\mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) &= \frac{e^{-\ell(\gamma)^2/2t}\ell(\gamma_0)e^{t\bar{K}(\gamma_0)/6}}{\sqrt{2\pi t\det{(I-P_\gamma)}}}(1 + O(t^2))
\end{aligned}
```

